	Lore: {
		FowlEmperorLore: {
			DisplayName: Fowl Emperor
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				I have traveled far in my conquest against the gods who call this world home.
				I have faced down both tricksters and murderers alike, from self-appointed righteous heroes to openly sadistic tyrants.
				Through this, I have faced warriors, beasts, demons, and all sorts. There is very little I haven’t experienced in this life.
				All of this is to say…
				WHAT!?
				'''
		}

		ErhanLore: {
			DisplayName: Erhan
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				A local priest, I assume? ‘Repent’, ‘heresy’, ‘judgement’... I’ve heard it all before.
				You hopefully don’t need me to tell you what happened to the various churches that once lined the surface.
				However, my reach doesn’t extend very far into those portals.
				The knowledge to make those portals is obscure, to say the least, and you’d be hard pressed to fit an army through the few that do exist.
				Further explanation is beyond our current perview, but I have no doubt whatever group this preacher hails from is on the other side. 
				Certainly explains why ‘his lands’ aren’t underground
				'''
		}

		ThornLore: {
			DisplayName: Thorn
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				I was wondering when someone would put this warden down.
				Alder was the name I heard some of the “treefolk” refer to him as.
				He, like those druids, is not native to this land, emerging from that portal on the surface.
				It’s connected to a forested area called fairwood, and in recent years has been subject to a mass exodus in order to escape a growing blight. 
				The rest weren’t much better, but this blighted freak is probably the worst of them, actively spreading whatever curse dwelled there. 
				I don’t believe those refugees have any idea what they’ve walked right into…
				'''
		}

		TheKeeperLore: {
			Tooltip: ""
			DisplayName: The Keeper
			Lore:
				'''
				Undead are commonplace no matter what part of the world you stand in.
				The way they are raised, however, can vary greatly. 
				In my brief studies through the portal, a common undead type occurs when a soul attempts to fuse with a vessel that isn’t its own.
				Usually, this creates a skeleton, which you’ve seen plenty of.
				If the soul is strong enough, pale brown flesh will form around the bone, creating what’s referred to as a fallen. 
				That’s certainly what this is… but I’ve never seen a fallen this feral before.
				And the way her body is mutated so severely, likely from whatever magic permeates her body… I’m genuinely curious.
				Actually, I still have those old scout reports documenting several different fallen, including info on the lives of a few.
				I’m certain she would’ve been noticed. Let’s see here…
				'''
		}

		SkullDiggerLore: {
			Tooltip: ""
			DisplayName: Skull Digger
			Lore:
				'''
				Another undead, with the same necromantic magic coursing through its body.
				I’m guessing Octavia used her magic to revive him, though at this point his body has started to fade away.
				…Ah, right. I’ve found those old fallen reports. I… believe I should read this section for you.

				Subject: Octavia Von Gailon

				Place of residence: Ricusa City, Ricusa - Lo Anglon

				Lifespan: Approx. 26 years

				Occupation: Musician - Violin

				Circumstances surrounding death: Recently confirmed pregnancy. Subject had purchased a teddy bear intended for the child the previous day.

				Cause of death: Found stabbed in an alleyway. Perpetrator unknown.

				…I suppose both of our worlds have a cruel sense of humor. If you could return that teddy bear back to her, I… I would appreciate that.
				I believe she would as well.
				'''
		}

		SeedofInfectionLore: {
			Tooltip: ""
			DisplayName: Seed of Infection
			Lore:
				'''
				Liden was another world with minor connections to ours. Quite frankly, I’ve had less reason to look into it than Epidotra. 
				The whole place is a frozen, radioactive wasteland, the likes of which . 
				I'm led to believe its current state stems from a lab overrun by a viscous infection: Xenomite.
				While this infected pocket wasn’t much of a threat, it wasn’t supposed to be.
				It has already done its job of spreading the infection in that area. 
				The only thing holding it back is the requirement of radiation in order to accelerate its growth.
				Unless you’re planning on setting off a nuke, the symptoms should be minor to non-existent.
				…Unless it somehow seeped into the sulphurous seas. Then it might be a problem.
				Damn it, Draedon.
				'''
		}

		EaglecrestGolemLore: {
			Tooltip: ""
			DisplayName: Eaglecrest Golem
			Lore:
				'''
				A peace offering from Gathuram to Ithon, as I understand it.
				Somehow, the fact it was built with inhabited stones escaped the notice of its makers before it was shipped off.
				Especially odd given the amount of constructs they’ve made from infusing stone with human souls.
				All magic uses the soul over there, even magical artifacts use a piece of the maker’s soul for casting. 
				Compared to our methods, theirs is far more complex to master, so understanding is typically limited to a select few with rudimentary skills. 
				Whatever soul is kept in this golem’s eye must be mighty to act on its own like this, more than a century after creation.
				'''
		}

		CalaviaLore: {
			Tooltip: ""
			DisplayName: Calavia
			Lore:
				'''
				You don’t speak gathic? Seems this could have been easily avoided, but regardless. 
				Due to the difficulty of travel between different planes, attempts at expansion across realms are often more trouble than they’re worth. 
				As such, my expeditions into this space were more focused on avoiding conflict and gathering knowledge.
				I had the benefit of being mostly unknown to its people, unlike here.
				I grew a cordial relationship with a few organizations, including the Barons of Arum, which gave me access to transfers with unique expertise on soul-based magic. 
				I immediately put it to use when I looked to power my newest soldiers.
				Their kingdoms weren’t happy to hear what their warriors’ souls were included in… but I got what I wanted.
				'''
		}

		AbandonedLaboratoryLore: {
			DisplayName: Abandoned Laboratory
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				I had no interest in the apocalyptic Liden, that radioactive graveyard was no place for living beings.
				Draedon, however, was more than willing to probe at his own discretion. 
				I thought little of it since his output was untouched, then he showed interest in that lab.
				He quickly penetrated the cyber security and monitored a handful of T-bots on the inside… that’s what he told me. 
				The fact his comms were briefly active during this mission gives me reason to believe he made contact with someone through its system.
				I never found out who or about what, the logs were never on record and Draedon has been cagey about it ever since. 
				He would leave my service soon after, for unrelated reasons, and the thread was cut before I could look into it. 
				It seems now, that thread is in your hands.
				'''
		}

		AncientDeityDuoLore: {
			DisplayName: Ancient Deity Duo
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				So, Epidotra had gods after all. 
				One sealed in stone, the other in deep sleep.
				Granted, I highly doubt these two stole their power like our gods,
				as the auric souls of life and storms were already claimed.
				Might not be gods as you and I know them, but merely magically adept.
				I assume so, but I know nothing of who these two were in the past.
				I could guess… but I’d prefer to know.
				What I know is what I see: 
				Two dead lovers.
				'''
		}

		KingSlayerIIILore: {
			DisplayName: King Slayer III
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				An armored… human? Automaton? I’ve heard an obscene number of descriptors given to him, all with equal evidence.
				His reputation is palpable, but word of mouth and misinformation have done a great disservice to him.
				Some is malicious gossip, some is genuine confusion. 
				I’ll admit, I’ve been quite unsure of this warrior ever since I first heard of him. 
				Even more confusingly, I’ve seen ancient statues that bear his exact visage, and there are things he is reported to have said that have… existential implications.
				Only he’d be able to clear that up, but you’d likely have to earn his favor first.
				After an encounter like that? 
				From personal experience, good luck.
				'''
		}

		ndOmegaPrototypeLore: {
			DisplayName: 2nd Omega Prototype
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				That confirms it.
				I don’t know how acquainted the two are, but Draedon must’ve had input here.
				This tunneler is modified in exactly the way he would’ve done it. I’m sure of it.
				Not to undermine the efforts of your benefactor, of course, who clearly led its creation.
				The armaments here are quite novel compared to my knights’. Excessive, perhaps.
				Knowing Draedon, he likely agreed to assist for the sake of research. How much, I’m not sure.
				No doubt he’ll look to optimize the sorry shield technology on display for himself.
				The other one, however… I know nothing about her.
				Expect anything.
				'''
		}

		NebuleusLore: {
			DisplayName: Nebuleus
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				...She approached me a few nights after you first arrived.
				I don’t know how, but she found her way into the Dragon Aerie.
				Despite our attempts at remaining polite, we got into an argument. 
				I called her naive. She called me a tyrant.
				I called her a coward. She called me conceited.
				…She left without a fight. 
				Truthfully, I don’t think she came here expecting to win one.
				She left with one last word…
				‘You saw a forest of predators and parasites.
				The trees called for your help, so you felled the ones who pruned the vines.
				You have none left, because their homes were lost while you weren’t looking.
				All that are left are the beasts you claimed to be culling.’
				…I feel like she premeditated that. Could’ve worked on it more.
				Doesn’t make it less true.
				'''
		}

		PatientZeroLore: {
			DisplayName: Patient Zero
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Kari Johanson. Original creator of the T-bots. What’s left of him, anyway.
				...Disgusting.
				I knew Liden pursued xenomite as a potent energy source.
				I also saw what became of that world, and knew not to follow.
				Those alien crystals were the source of this horrific mutation, the first of the lot,
				and 50 years later, the entire lab is a breeding ground while the surface suffered a nuclear apocalypse.
				I’d say it has more in common with the astral infection than any disease you or I know.
				Killing him likely slowed down its spread... for all the good that did.
				A whole planet, wiped away because of financial interest…
				I hope that isn’t in our future.
				'''
		}

		rdOmegaPrototypeLore: {
			DisplayName: 3rd Omega Prototype
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				And here, the difference in personality is on full display.
				No, I’m not referring to the machine’s actual personality.
				My soldiers were weapons of war, first and foremost.
				Frontline, backline, assault, support. There was a purpose to each.
				This machine is a weapon and nothing else. 
				It’s a blunt instrument built to cause as much damage as possible.
				There’s a place for that, but not in conquest.
				Now, I see the other end of the deal.
				These aren’t tools built for tactical purposes, it was rage that made this.
				Pure rage.
				I fear an already capable mind like that picking at Draedon’s intellect.
				'''
		}

		stOmegaPrototypeLore: {
			DisplayName: 1st Omega Prototype
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				It seems whoever was at the lab has made herself known.
				This is quite an entrance for a burgeoning inventor, albeit an impractical device. 
				It's easy to understand why Teochrome went defunct in hindsight.
				Sure, xenomite seems like a fine source of energy… until you notice the many caveats.
				The fact this managed to perform on my soldiers’ level at all is praiseworthy,
				if this prototype really was a proof of concept lying around. 
				I might've sought out that prowess all those years back.
				'''
		}
	}

